Task 1: Install and Configure SpiderFoot
Step 1: Install SpiderFoot
# Update system and install dependencies
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y python3 python3-pip git

# Clone SpiderFoot repository
cd /opt
sudo git clone https://github.com/smicallef/spiderfoot.git
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/spiderfoot

# Install Python dependencies
cd /opt/spiderfoot
pip3 install -r requirements.txt
Step 2: Start SpiderFoot Web Interface
# Start SpiderFoot on localhost
cd /opt/spiderfoot
python3 sf.py -l 127.0.0.1:5001
Open a web browser and navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5001 to verify installation.

Step 3: Configure Your First Scan
Click New Scan in the SpiderFoot interface

Configure scan settings:

Scan Name: Lab_Relationship_Mapping
Target: Use a legitimate educational target (e.g., example.edu)
Target Type: Select Domain Name
Enable these modules:

DNS resolver
Web spider
Email harvester
WHOIS lookups
Certificate transparency logs
Click Run Scan and monitor progress

Step 4: Export Scan Results
Once the scan completes (15-30 minutes):

Navigate to your scan results
Click Export and select CSV format
Save to /home/$USER/spiderfoot_export.csv
