Troubleshooting Tips
SpiderFoot Issues
Problem: SpiderFoot web interface not accessible

Solution: Check if the service is running: ps aux | grep sf.py
Restart SpiderFoot: cd /opt/spiderfoot && python3 sf.py -l 127.0.0.1:5001
Problem: Scan fails or returns no results

Solution: Verify target is accessible and properly formatted
Check module configuration and API keys if required
Review SpiderFoot logs for errors
Maltego Issues
Problem: Maltego fails to start

Solution: Reinstall with sudo apt-get install -f
Check Java installation: java -version
Problem: Transforms not working

Solution: Verify Transform Hub installations
Check API key configuration for external services
Ensure internet connectivity
Python Script Issues
Problem: Import errors for networkx or matplotlib

Solution: Reinstall packages: pip3 install --upgrade networkx matplotlib
Use virtual environment if conflicts occur
Problem: CSV parsing errors

Solution: Verify CSV file format and encoding
Check for special characters or malformed data
Use try-except blocks for robust error handling
